-- Samsung Total Petrochemicals Shuts Naphtha Cracker After Power Disruption
-- Shinhye Kang
-- 2010-07-23T03:14:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/samsung-total-petrochemicals-shuts-naphtha-cracker-after-power-disruption.html

          
          
             Samsung Total Petrochemicals Co.
shut its naphtha cracker today at Daesan complex in South Korea
after a thunderstorm disrupted power supply, a company official
said. The 850,000 metric ton-a-year plant was shut around 10
a.m.  local time today and may resume operation in about one or
two days, said the official, who declined to be identified
because he isnâ€™t authorized to speak to the media.  
